URL: https://bioconductor.org/packages/universalmotif/
BugReports: https://github.com/bjmt/universalmotif/issues
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for working with sequence motifs in R.
    Imports and exports most common motif formats (JASPAR, MEME, HOMER,
    TRANSFAC, CIS-BP, UNIPROBE) and interoperates with the other Bioconductor
    motif packages. Analysis functions cover de novo motif discovery,
    motif-vs-motif comparison and clustering, P-value calculation, sequence
    scanning, enrichment against shuffled or composition-matched backgrounds,
    positional bias testing, and pairwise motif co-occurrence. Also
    includes utilities for sequence shuffling, motif trimming, higher-order
    representations, ground-truth simulation by motif implantation, and
    logo-plotting functionality.
